97
00:06:34.627 --> 00:06:38.027
and as a token of her appreciation, Yoko treated Mr. Higo to a meal.

98
00:06:38.927 --> 00:06:41.227
Yoko doesn't have a kid brother.

99
00:06:41.227 --> 00:06:45.027
Rather, why is she asking Mr. Higo to pick it out for her?

100
00:06:45.027 --> 00:06:46.427
I don't get it!

101
00:06:46.427 --> 00:06:48.027
I guess not.

102
00:06:48.027 --> 00:06:51.327
Then, maybe those two are going with each other after all.

103
00:06:53.727 --> 00:06:56.527
Sorry! Forget what I said. Forget it!

104
00:06:56.527 --> 00:06:59.527
Why don't you go over to that restaurant then?

105
00:06:59.527 --> 00:07:01.927
But the name of the restaurant's not written!

106
00:07:01.927 --> 00:07:04.927
Come to think of it, I heard one of Mr. Higo's soccer club seniors

107
00:07:04.927 --> 00:07:06.827
who retired from the J-League

108
00:07:06.827 --> 00:07:10.027
opened an Italian restaurant in Haidocho.

109
00:07:10.027 --> 00:07:11.827
Where's that shop?

110
00:07:11.827 --> 00:07:15.027
But I don't know if they're really at that shop.

111
00:07:16.427 --> 00:07:19.027
They're here. Both of them.

112
00:07:19.027 --> 00:07:20.727
And more so...

113
00:07:20.727 --> 00:07:22.727
From the way that these two are acting,

114
00:07:22.727 --> 00:07:25.227
it's no wonder Ran didn't want to come along.

115
00:07:26.827 --> 00:07:28.927
Hey, what're you taking notes of?

116
00:07:28.927 --> 00:07:32.127
The number of times that idol smiled at Mr. Higo!

117
00:07:34.127 --> 00:07:38.827
Hey. Didn't you like Yoko Okino's songs and listen to them repeatedly?

118
00:07:38.827 --> 00:07:41.227
I deleted all of them just a while ago.

119
00:07:42.427 --> 00:07:44.127
And?

120
00:07:44.127 --> 00:07:47.427
Is he the senior of that soccer guy?

121
00:07:47.427 --> 00:07:49.127
What?

122
00:07:49.127 --> 00:07:51.127
Nope.

123
00:07:51.127 --> 00:07:53.827
Mr. Higo's senior is Teiya Asuka,

124
00:07:53.827 --> 00:07:55.927
who used to be a wing back for the Tokyo Spirits,

125
00:07:55.927 --> 00:07:59.327
and was even chosen as a representative for Japan, too.

126
00:07:59.327 --> 00:08:03.427
I think he's the sommelier for this restaurant.

127
00:08:03.427 --> 00:08:07.627
I wonder what that guy intends to do after getting Yoko drunk?

128
00:08:07.627 --> 00:08:08.927
What?

129
00:08:11.127 --> 00:08:13.627
Where's Mr. Asuka?

130
00:08:13.627 --> 00:08:15.127
The owner's out buying some wine...

131
00:08:15.127 --> 00:08:19.127
"Akimichi Yamada (43), Sommelier" -and should be back soon.

132
00:08:20.027 --> 00:08:23.027
Should I tell him to come to your table when he gets back?

133
00:08:23.027 --> 00:08:24.927
Yes, please do that.

134
00:08:24.927 --> 00:08:27.727
Please enjoy.

135
00:08:27.727 --> 00:08:29.227
"Reiko Banba (27), waitress" -Excuse me.

136
00:08:29.227 --> 00:08:31.527
Here's your dessert.

137
00:08:33.927 --> 00:08:36.227
I'm so sorry!

138
00:08:36.227 --> 00:08:38.927
What an amateur, that waitress.

139
00:08:38.927 --> 00:08:41.827
Maybe she was distracted looking at Mr. Higo.

140
00:08:47.227 --> 00:08:48.627
I goofed.

141
00:08:48.627 --> 00:08:51.727
That guy Higo is the owner's friend, right?

142
00:08:51.727 --> 00:08:54.727
If he was here, you would've really gotten it from the owner.

143
00:08:54.727 --> 00:08:56.127
No problem.

144
00:08:56.127 --> 00:08:59.927
He never gets angry at me.

145
00:08:59.927 --> 00:09:03.527
Don't let it get to your head, just because you're going with him.

146
00:09:03.527 --> 00:09:04.727
Talk for yourself.

147
00:09:04.727 --> 00:09:08.227
Don't let it get to you just because you're my ex.

148
00:09:09.827 --> 00:09:13.127
"Yasuto Konoe (28), waiter"

149
00:09:13.927 --> 00:09:16.827
The owner sure is late, though.

150
00:09:16.827 --> 00:09:19.327
It's about time he should be back already.

151
00:09:19.327 --> 00:09:21.627
Shall we go look for him?

152
00:09:21.627 --> 00:09:23.327
I guess so.

153
00:09:23.327 --> 00:09:26.427
Mr. Konoe and I will go check the back room then.

154
00:09:26.427 --> 00:09:27.627
Yes, sir.

155
00:09:29.827 --> 00:09:32.827
Ms. Banba, please check the storeroom.

156
00:09:32.827 --> 00:09:34.227
Okay!

157
00:09:36.827 --> 00:09:38.627
He's not here.

158
00:09:38.627 --> 00:09:42.127
He always takes short naps on this sofa, but...

159
00:09:42.127 --> 00:09:45.027
He didn't seem to be getting enough sleep lately.

160
00:09:47.227 --> 00:09:51.427
Come to think of it, weren't you arguing with the owner last night?

161
00:09:51.427 --> 00:09:54.227
He complained that the wine I buy is too expensive.

162
00:09:54.227 --> 00:09:57.527
Well, I guess it can't be helped because he owns this restaurant.

163
00:09:57.527 --> 00:09:59.927
He isn't in the storeroom either.

164
00:09:59.927 --> 00:10:02.527
Shall we wait for him a while longer then?

165
00:10:02.527 --> 00:10:04.227
-Yes. -Okay.

166
00:10:06.627 --> 00:10:08.627
They're asking for Mr. Asuka again.

167
00:10:08.627 --> 00:10:11.427
They want to know if he came back.

168
00:10:11.427 --> 00:10:13.127
What shall we do?

169
00:10:13.127 --> 00:10:15.027
Shall we go look for him again?

170
00:10:15.027 --> 00:10:16.927
Maybe we should check the bathroom just in case, too.

171
00:10:16.927 --> 00:10:20.227
-Yes. -I'll go check the bathroom then!

172
00:10:20.227 --> 00:10:21.927
Thanks.

173
00:10:26.927 --> 00:10:29.727
He's not in the storeroom.

174
00:10:29.727 --> 00:10:32.427
He's not in the bathroom, either.

175
00:10:32.427 --> 00:10:34.027
I found the owner.

176
00:10:34.027 --> 00:10:36.227
It seems he's taking a nap on the sofa.

177
00:10:36.227 --> 00:10:37.227
No joke?

178
00:10:37.227 --> 00:10:40.627
Yes. He has a blanket over his head.

179
00:10:40.627 --> 00:10:43.527
He doesn't know that his friend is here?

180
00:10:43.527 --> 00:10:47.227
Let's let him sleep another 10 minutes then wake him up.

181
00:10:51.527 --> 00:10:53.927
It's almost 10 minutes.

182
00:10:53.927 --> 00:10:58.427
I'll go to the back room and wake the owner up then.

183
00:10:58.427 --> 00:11:00.027
Okay.

184
00:11:06.727 --> 00:11:09.427
It's e-mail from the owner.

185
00:11:09.427 --> 00:11:12.727
"Could you bring Higo and Yoko over to the storeroom

186
00:11:12.727 --> 00:11:14.327
without anyone noticing?"

187
00:11:14.327 --> 00:11:17.227
So he got up on his own?

188
00:11:17.227 --> 00:11:20.027
I'll take the two over to the back room then.

189
00:11:20.027 --> 00:11:21.127
Thanks.

190
00:11:25.227 --> 00:11:26.727
What's going on?

191
00:11:26.727 --> 00:11:28.927
It seems they're going somewhere.

192
00:11:33.527 --> 00:11:37.427
Why does that girl idol have to stand so close to him?

193
00:11:37.427 --> 00:11:41.027
That soccer guy walks too slow!

194
00:11:41.027 --> 00:11:43.727
I guess I'll go take a puff in the restroom then.

195
00:11:43.727 --> 00:11:47.227
Hey, it's no smoking in the restroom too, normally, isn't it?

196
00:11:48.427 --> 00:11:50.127
But when I went to the restroom a while ago,

197
00:11:50.127 --> 00:11:52.527
I smelled cigarettes.

198
00:11:52.527 --> 00:11:54.027
What? Really?

199
00:11:54.027 --> 00:11:55.127
Yeah.

200
00:11:57.527 --> 00:11:59.527
That was Yoko's scream!

201
00:12:00.827 --> 00:12:02.427
Where did they go?

202
00:12:02.427 --> 00:12:04.827
To... to the basement storeroom.

203
00:12:04.827 --> 00:12:08.827
Don't tell me that the soccer guy did something terrible to Yoko.

204
00:12:09.727 --> 00:12:11.127
Yoko!

205
00:12:17.727 --> 00:12:19.227
Hey, Mr. Asuka?

206
00:12:19.227 --> 00:12:21.127
Get a hold of yourself! Hey!

207
00:12:21.127 --> 00:12:22.627
Mr. Asuka?

208
00:12:22.627 --> 00:12:24.027
Mr. Asuka!

209
00:12:32.994 --> 00:12:35.994
The victim is the owner of this restaurant,

210
00:12:35.994 --> 00:12:38.394
Mr. Teiya Asuka, age 31.

211
00:12:38.394 --> 00:12:39.994
The ETD is during the hour,

212
00:12:39.994 --> 00:12:43.594
between a little after 19:00 to a little before 20:00.

213
00:12:43.594 --> 00:12:46.694
The cause of death is blood loss due to a severed carotid artery.

214
00:12:46.694 --> 00:12:50.694
The murder weapon is a cutter knife that was found near the corpse.

215
00:12:50.694 --> 00:12:54.194
It seems that one of the cutter knives

216
00:12:54.194 --> 00:12:56.494
that was in the back room is missing,

217
00:12:56.494 --> 00:12:58.094
that most likely is it.

218
00:12:58.094 --> 00:12:59.294
I see.

219
00:12:59.294 --> 00:13:01.994
And? The first discoverers of the corpse,

220
00:13:01.994 --> 00:13:04.694
are you who were here at this restaurant,

221
00:13:04.694 --> 00:13:07.194
Mr. Ryusuke Higo, a J-Leaguer

222
00:13:07.194 --> 00:13:10.294
and idol Ms. Yoko Okino?

223
00:13:10.294 --> 00:13:11.294
-Yes. -Yes.

224
00:13:11.294 --> 00:13:14.894
But, why did you come to the storeroom when you came as customers?

225
00:13:14.894 --> 00:13:18.094
The waiter brought us here.

226
00:13:18.094 --> 00:13:21.394
He said that he received e-mail from Mr. Asuka

227
00:13:21.394 --> 00:13:22.694
telling him to bring us here.

228
00:13:22.694 --> 00:13:24.994
Did you know the victim?

229
00:13:24.994 --> 00:13:29.094
Yes. Mr. Asuka is an OB of the soccer club of our high school,

230
00:13:29.094 --> 00:13:32.194
