even before the body was found, you know?

252
00:14:34.994 --> 00:14:36.794
Running around?

253
00:14:36.794 --> 00:14:39.694
Oh, right. The owner wasn't back for some time,

254
00:14:39.694 --> 00:14:42.394
so we decided to split up and go look for him.

255
00:14:42.394 --> 00:14:44.294
He sometimes comes back without saying anything

256
00:14:44.294 --> 00:14:46.494
and takes short naps in the back room, you see.

257
00:14:46.494 --> 00:14:49.494
And there were customers who wanted to see him too, so...

258
00:14:49.494 --> 00:14:51.994
I think the first time was around 7:00 p.m.?

259
00:14:51.994 --> 00:14:54.894
So, I went with him to check the back room.

260
00:14:54.894 --> 00:14:58.894
And I had her go and check the storeroom.

261
00:14:58.894 --> 00:15:01.194
The back room?

262
00:15:01.194 --> 00:15:04.294
It's where the staff takes a break. It's this room.

263
00:15:06.394 --> 00:15:08.294
And where was he taking a nap?

264
00:15:08.294 --> 00:15:09.894
On this sofa.

265
00:15:09.894 --> 00:15:11.794
But when we came here the first time,

266
00:15:11.794 --> 00:15:13.994
the only thing here was the blanket

267
00:15:13.994 --> 00:15:15.694
and there was no one here.

268
00:15:17.794 --> 00:15:20.494
When you searched the storeroom,

269
00:15:20.494 --> 00:15:22.694
you didn't see the owner there?

270
00:15:22.694 --> 00:15:23.694
No.

271
00:15:23.694 --> 00:15:28.094
But the next time, I was told to search the back room

272
00:15:28.094 --> 00:15:31.894
so I went back about 10 minutes later.

273
00:15:31.894 --> 00:15:35.194
Then, I found the owner there.

274
00:15:35.194 --> 00:15:36.994
-You found the owner? -Yes.

275
00:15:36.994 --> 00:15:40.894
He was sleeping on the sofa with a blanket over his head.

276
00:15:40.894 --> 00:15:44.694
His shoes were placed near the sofa too, so I'm sure!

277
00:15:44.694 --> 00:15:48.294
But... But, why was the owner...

278
00:15:50.494 --> 00:15:52.494
And, what after that?

279
00:15:52.494 --> 00:15:54.394
After she told me this,

280
00:15:54.394 --> 00:15:57.294
I went to wake him up about 10 minutes later.

281
00:15:57.294 --> 00:15:59.794
Back then, he wasn't asleep on the sofa.

282
00:15:59.794 --> 00:16:03.394
Just about that time, I got an e-mail from the owner

283
00:16:03.394 --> 00:16:05.894
telling me if I could bring Mr. Higo and Yoko to the storeroom

284
00:16:05.894 --> 00:16:08.294
without being noticed by anyone.

285
00:16:09.394 --> 00:16:11.394
About what time was it?

286
00:16:11.394 --> 00:16:13.994
About 7:30 p.m.

287
00:16:13.994 --> 00:16:18.094
That's why I brought those two to the storeroom, you see.

288
00:16:18.094 --> 00:16:20.294
I called him just before going into the storeroom,

289
00:16:20.294 --> 00:16:21.894
but there was no answer.

290
00:16:21.894 --> 00:16:23.394
Since he didn't come out,

291
00:16:23.394 --> 00:16:25.794
I thought he went back to the back room.

292
00:16:25.794 --> 00:16:29.194
I left the two at the storeroom and went to the back room,

293
00:16:29.194 --> 00:16:31.194
but only Mr. Yamada was there.

294
00:16:31.194 --> 00:16:34.894
When all three of us were wondering where the owner went...

295
00:16:34.894 --> 00:16:37.194
We heard Yoko scream.

296
00:16:37.194 --> 00:16:39.394
And just as we were about to head over to the storeroom,

297
00:16:39.394 --> 00:16:41.794
Detective Mouri came.

298
00:16:41.794 --> 00:16:44.394
Spit it out! I'll bet you persistently asked Yoko

299
00:16:44.394 --> 00:16:45.894
to come to this restaurant with you?

300
00:16:45.894 --> 00:16:46.894
No.

301
00:16:46.894 --> 00:16:49.494
I'll bet you're the one that asked him to come?

302
00:16:49.494 --> 00:16:50.794
What?

303
00:16:50.794 --> 00:16:53.694
Just what are they investigating anyway?

304
00:16:53.694 --> 00:16:56.594
Which means you found the corpse while you were waiting at the storeroom?

305
00:16:56.594 --> 00:16:59.694
Yes. Since they didn't come back for a while,

306
00:16:59.694 --> 00:17:02.094
we were looking around the storeroom and...

307
00:17:02.094 --> 00:17:04.994
I think it was around 7:50 p.m.

308
00:17:04.994 --> 00:17:08.694
7:50 p.m. is just barely within the estimated time of death.

309
00:17:08.694 --> 00:17:11.494
Yeah, which makes these two suspects, too.

310
00:17:11.494 --> 00:17:13.394
What?

311
00:17:13.394 --> 00:17:14.894
Anyway, everyone...

312
00:17:14.894 --> 00:17:17.194
I'll have to talk to all of you individually.

313
00:17:18.194 --> 00:17:19.994
Like I said a while ago,

314
00:17:19.994 --> 00:17:22.194
I couldn't have committed the crime.

315
00:17:22.194 --> 00:17:24.194
When I first came to search for the owner,

316
00:17:24.194 --> 00:17:26.394
I was in this back room with Mr. Yamada,

317
00:17:26.394 --> 00:17:28.094
and next I was checking the men's room.

318
00:17:28.094 --> 00:17:31.094
Then, finally, I took those two to the storeroom,

319
00:17:31.094 --> 00:17:33.494
but I just called out from outside the storeroom

320
00:17:33.494 --> 00:17:35.394
and didn't go inside.

321
00:17:35.394 --> 00:17:40.194
That's why, while Ms. Banba was serving food and wine,

322
00:17:40.194 --> 00:17:41.494
you could've pretended to go to the restroom

323
00:17:41.494 --> 00:17:43.094
and snuck off to the storeroom.

324
00:17:43.094 --> 00:17:46.894
No way! The storeroom's always locked.

325
00:17:46.894 --> 00:17:50.094
And the key is always hung on the wall at the entrance of the corridor

326
00:17:50.094 --> 00:17:52.794
so that the staff can always keep an eye on it.

327
00:17:52.794 --> 00:17:55.494
Why is it put where the staff can keep an eye on it?

328
00:17:55.494 --> 00:17:57.794
In the past, there were staff who would come to the storeroom

329
00:17:57.794 --> 00:18:00.894
and this back room to smoke.

330
00:18:00.894 --> 00:18:03.094
The owner did it to prevent this from happening again.

331
00:18:03.094 --> 00:18:05.594
And besides, he hated cigarettes.

332
00:18:05.594 --> 00:18:08.194
Which means this room is always locked, too?

333
00:18:08.194 --> 00:18:10.394
Yes, and the back door, too.

334
00:18:10.394 --> 00:18:13.694
Only the owner had the spare key!

335
00:18:13.694 --> 00:18:16.594
Did the victim have the spare keys on him?

336
00:18:16.594 --> 00:18:19.294
Yes, inside the pocket of his slacks.

337
00:18:19.294 --> 00:18:22.794
But the cell phone of the victim wasn't found,

338
00:18:22.794 --> 00:18:26.294
so the forensics are looking for it now in the storeroom.

339
00:18:26.294 --> 00:18:28.194
I see.

340
00:18:28.194 --> 00:18:30.994
At any rate, I didn't do it.

341
00:18:30.994 --> 00:18:34.094
I've got nothing against the owner besides.

342
00:18:34.094 --> 00:18:37.394
I hear you're the one that's been smoking in this room.

343
00:18:37.394 --> 00:18:40.294
-What? -The waitress told me a while ago.

344
00:18:40.294 --> 00:18:42.794
That the owner was bawling you out.

345
00:18:42.794 --> 00:18:44.194
Was that your motive?

346
00:18:44.194 --> 00:18:46.694
No. That's...

347
00:18:46.694 --> 00:18:49.794
If you're the perp, will you please hurry up and confess?

348
00:18:49.794 --> 00:18:51.194
What?

349
00:18:51.194 --> 00:18:52.194
If you're talking about motive,

350
00:18:52.194 --> 00:18:55.094
I think the other two have more motive than I do.

351
00:18:55.094 --> 00:18:56.794
What?

352
00:18:56.794 --> 00:18:58.594
The sommelier Mr. Yamada

353
00:18:58.594 --> 00:19:01.594
had an argument with the owner over wine last night.

354
00:19:01.594 --> 00:19:05.494
And the waitress Reiko Banba is the owner's girlfriend, you know?

355
00:19:05.494 --> 00:19:06.794
Girlfriend?

356
00:19:08.094 --> 00:19:11.594
Maybe she killed him over a messy break up something?

357
00:19:12.894 --> 00:19:14.394
Yes, that's right.

358
00:19:14.394 --> 00:19:16.994
I was going with the owner,

359
00:19:16.994 --> 00:19:18.994
but there was no talk about a break up!

360
00:19:18.994 --> 00:19:21.594
But the waiter Mr. Konoe mentioned that

361
00:19:21.594 --> 00:19:25.294
the owner hadn't been going home with you lately.

362
00:19:25.294 --> 00:19:27.994
That's because he was sleeping over here,

363
00:19:27.994 --> 00:19:31.794
so that he could think of ways to make business more profitable!

364
00:19:31.794 --> 00:19:33.394
He was sleeping over here.

365
00:19:33.394 --> 00:19:37.194
Right. That's why the owner's locker at the very left

366
00:19:37.194 --> 00:19:39.094
is full of a change of clothes, isn't it?

367
00:19:42.394 --> 00:19:44.194
True.

368
00:19:44.194 --> 00:19:46.494
There's even a change of shoes here.

369
00:19:46.494 --> 00:19:48.994
I'll bet Mr. Konoe is saying things like that

370
00:19:48.994 --> 00:19:52.994
because he used to be my ex-boyfriend and is jealous.

371
00:19:52.994 --> 00:19:55.394
Your ex-boyfriend?

372
00:19:55.394 --> 00:19:58.294
But if he had the blanket over his head

373
00:19:58.294 --> 00:20:00.294
when he was sleeping on the sofa,

374
00:20:00.294 --> 00:20:02.094
you didn't see his face, right?

375
00:20:02.094 --> 00:20:03.694
No, I guess not.

376
00:20:03.694 --> 00:20:07.694
Then maybe you could put something under the blanket

377
00:20:07.694 --> 00:20:10.294
to make it look as if he were sleeping there, couldn't you?

378
00:20:10.294 --> 00:20:14.494
What? What good is it for me to do something like that?

379
00:20:14.494 --> 00:20:16.994
When you first went to look for the owner in the storeroom,

380
00:20:16.994 --> 00:20:19.394
you could've actually killed him.

381
00:20:19.394 --> 00:20:21.594
Then after that, to make it look as if he were still alive,

382
00:20:21.594 --> 00:20:23.394
you faked the scene, didn't you?

383
00:20:23.394 --> 00:20:25.794
When I came to search this room,

384
00:20:25.794 --> 00:20:29.494
Mr. Yamada the sommelier was at the storeroom, you know?

385
00:20:29.494 --> 00:20:31.994
If Mr. Yamada found the owner's body,

386
00:20:31.994 --> 00:20:34.694
everything would be in vain, right?

387
00:20:34.694 --> 00:20:38.794
This room is really tidy.

388
00:20:38.794 --> 00:20:40.394
Of course.

389
00:20:40.394 --> 00:20:43.194
Because the owner would stay back after work

390
00:20:43.194 --> 00:20:44.994
and clean the room all by himself.

391
00:20:44.994 --> 00:20:47.494
The owner was a tidy person, wasn't he?

392
00:20:47.494 --> 00:20:50.694
Yes. Because even after I cleaned the place thoroughly,

393
00:20:50.694 --> 00:20:52.794
I could hear the sound of the vacuum cleaner.

394
00:20:52.794 --> 00:20:56.494
I think he was vacuuming really small dust that couldn't be noticed.

395
00:20:57.994 --> 00:21:01.394
What? You mean when I went to look for him in the storeroom?

396
00:21:01.394 --> 00:21:04.094
The owner wasn't there,

397
00:21:04.094 --> 00:21:05.994
but I did the same thing as Mr. Konoe

398
00:21:05.994 --> 00:21:08.894
and just called him from the entrance.

399
00:21:08.894 --> 00:21:11.194
Which means he may have already been killed

400
00:21:11.194 --> 00:21:14.294
inside the storeroom at that time?

401
00:21:14.294 --> 00:21:16.194
Yes, I guess so.

402
00:21:16.194 --> 00:21:20.494
By the way, it seems that you had an argument with the owner last night.

403
00:21:20.494 --> 00:21:24.294
Yes. The restaurant hasn't been doing well lately,

404
00:21:24.294 --> 00:21:25.894
so the owner said he wanted to stock inexpensive wine

405
00:21:25.894 --> 00:21:27.794
in place of the expensive ones.

406
00:21:27.794 --> 00:21:30.994
I only expressed my concern over that because this restaurant

407
00:21:30.994 --> 00:21:33.894
was supposed to be an authentic, very Italian restaurant.

408
00:21:33.894 --> 00:21:36.594
-That's why you killed him? -What?

409
00:21:36.594 --> 00:21:39.594
You mean you did it to so you could buy expensive wine of your taste.

410
00:21:39.594 --> 00:21:40.994
With the owner dead,

411
00:21:40.994 --> 00:21:43.594
I wouldn't be able to buy them if I wanted to!

412
00:21:43.594 --> 00:21:45.694
Inspector!

413
00:21:45.694 --> 00:21:50.594
A lot of cigarette butts were found in the trash box of the restroom.

414
00:21:50.594 --> 00:21:52.894
I thought the restroom was no smoking, too?

415
00:21:52.894 --> 00:21:56.094
Yes, I think it's Mr. Konoe.

416
00:21:56.094 --> 00:21:58.494
He used to smoke in this room before,

417
00:21:58.494 --> 00:22:00.494
but after being scolded by the owner,

418
00:22:00.494 --> 00:22:03.494
I think he hid in the restroom and smoked.

419
00:22:03.494 --> 00:22:07.494
If in the restroom, he could say that a customer smoked.

420
00:22:07.494 --> 00:22:10.194
That's why the restroom smelled of cigarettes.

421
00:22:10.194 --> 00:22:11.494
Come to think of it,

422
00:22:11.494 --> 00:22:15.494
he said from himself that he'd search the restroom,

423
00:22:15.494 --> 00:22:18.894
so maybe he didn't want anyone noticing the smell of cigarettes.

424
00:22:22.594 --> 00:22:24.494
Although there are 5 suspects,

425
00:22:24.494 --> 00:22:26.494
the suspicious ones are those three.

426
00:22:28.794 --> 00:22:33.394
How on earth did the perp commit the crime?

427
00:23:54.294 --> 00:23:56.594
"Next Episode" -There's a tiny hole.

428
00:23:56.594 --> 00:23:59.594
Hey, is that blood?

429
00:23:59.594 --> 00:24:03.494
Only Mr. Higo or Yoko who were waiting in the storeroom

430
00:24:03.494 --> 00:24:06.294
could've committed the crime.

431
00:24:06.294 --> 00:24:10.594
-What? -Wait... wait a minute, Inspector!

432
00:24:10.594 --> 00:24:12.994
They wanted a third party

433
00:24:12.994 --> 00:24:16.294
to confirm that the owner wasn't in the room

434
00:24:16.294 --> 00:24:18.194
So, give yourself up!

435
00:24:18.994 --> 00:24:20.494
Next Conan,

436
00:24:20.494 --> 00:24:24.294
"The Suspects are Passionate Lovers (Part 2)"

437
00:24:24.837 --> 00:24:27.237
Next Conan's Hint:

438
00:24:27.237 --> 00:24:29.537
"Vacuum bag"

439
00:24:29.537 --> 00:24:31.337
-Yoko! -Something is definitely strange, after all!

440
00:24:31.337 --> 00:24:32.937
I'll never let this couple be...

441
00:24:32.937 --> 00:24:34.337
Perfect sync.

